---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';

const updated = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
---

<!-- LEGAL REVIEW NEEDED: placeholder copy -->
<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description={`Privacy policy for ${SITE.name}.`}>
  <p class="review-note">
    LEGAL REVIEW NEEDED — this is placeholder copy. Final wording comes from the
    OAuth research document before public launch.
  </p>

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="muted">Last updated: {updated}</p>

  <p class="lede">
    {SITE.name} is a desktop application. It runs entirely on your computer and
    is designed so that your data stays on your device.
  </p>

  <h2>Data we access</h2>
  <p>
    When you connect a streaming account, {SITE.name} requests an OAuth access
    token (and, where applicable, a refresh token) from that platform. These
    tokens authorize {SITE.name} to start broadcasts and read basic channel
    information on your behalf. {SITE.name} requests the minimum scopes required
    to enable streaming.
  </p>

  <h2>Where your data is stored</h2>
  <p>
    OAuth tokens and connection settings are stored locally on your device and
    are encrypted at rest. On Windows this uses the operating system's Data
    Protection API (DPAPI), which binds the encrypted data to your user account.
    {SITE.name} does not transmit these tokens to any server operated by us.
  </p>

  <h2>Data we do not collect</h2>
  <p>
    We do not operate an account system and we do not send your personal data,
    credentials, or stream content to our own servers. Your broadcast media
    travels directly from your device to the streaming platforms you connect.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    When you choose to connect a platform, your use of that platform is governed
    by its own privacy policy and terms:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Google / YouTube (YouTube Live streaming)</li>
    <li>Twitch</li>
    <li>Kick</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    {SITE.name} interacts with these services only to authenticate your account
    and manage your broadcasts, using the tokens described above.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention and deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Because tokens are stored only on your device, you remain in control of them
    at all times. You can disconnect a platform inside {SITE.name} to remove its
    stored tokens, or delete the application's local configuration to remove all
    stored data. You may also revoke {SITE.name}'s access at any time from the
    security settings of the connected platform.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE.name} is not directed to children and does not knowingly collect
    information from them.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy as the application evolves. Material changes will
    be reflected on this page with a new "last updated" date.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy can be sent to
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
